          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Process Mining",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "38 university students",
          "1 English as Second Language Course",
          "LMS logs, Eye-Tracking Data, Conversational transcripts",
          "Help-seeking process model",
          "[Diagnosing Question, Asking Help Instrumental, Asking Help Executive, Asking Help Avoidant, Asking Help Clarifying, Asking Help Understanding, Evaluating Help Positive, Evaluating Help No Feedback, Evaluating Help Negative, Processing Help Accepting, Processing Help Neglecting, Processing Help Returning]",
          "Data collected from the different sources is aggregated into each construct of help-seeking. \n\nThe processes are measured in relative terms.",
          "First Order Markov Models",
          "Differences between HE group and ChatGPT is done using a Shapiro-Wilk test. Effect size of AI presence is done using Cliff’s delta.\n\nFOMM rules needed at least a 5% threshold of transitions. ",
          "2",
          "-",
          "Students wityh access to AI have shown a much higher propensity to ask for help than their peers. LEarners without access to it are much more likely to critically try to engage with questions before going through with asking for help.\n\nMoreover, students without access to AI are much more likely to follow through with the standard linear  help-seeking process. Access to AI often skips critical steps: Diagnosing Question and Evaluating Answer.",
          "Work does a comparison between help-seeking behaviors for essay writing of learners using ChatGPT vs students who do not have access to ChatGPT.\n\nGroups were set experimentally Apriori.",
          "Difficulty in measuring cognitive processes exclusively using behavioral data.\n\nHuman interactions were not done in a naturalistic classroom setting. \n\nSmall sample size in the context of a single course.\n\nNo analysis of context of quality of the help provided (authors measure the act of seeking help). \n\nRequires validation for learning tasks beyond essay writing."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
