    {
      "id": "18d4750c-f3ba-801d-bddd-c396567294b6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Results show that Human help-seeking is linear, whilst AI group follows a more non-linear approach to help-seeking. Also, in human help-seeking there seems to be more thought put into the analysis of the feedback that is received, showing that it is possible that student over-rely on AI when it is available (since they ask pretty much everything).",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "18d4750c-f3ba-801d-bddd-c396567294b6",
        "parent": {
